Module kivakit.component
Package com.telenav.kivakit.component

Interface Component

All Superinterfaces:
Broadcaster, JavaTrait, LanguageTrait, Listener, NamedObject, PackageTrait, ProjectTrait, Receiver, RegistryTrait, Repeater, ResultTrait, SettingsTrait, SilentTryTrait, Transceiver, Transmitter, TripwireTrait, TryTrait
All Known Subinterfaces:
ComponentMixin
All Known Implementing Classes:
Application, BaseComponent, Server
public interface Component extends JavaTrait, ProjectTrait, PackageTrait, RegistryTrait, LanguageTrait, SettingsTrait, Repeater, NamedObject
A composite interface providing convenient functionality to KivaKit components.

Sub-Interfaces

  • PackageTrait - Access to packages and packaged resources
  • SettingsTrait - Component settings
  • RegistryTrait - Service Registry access
  • LanguageTrait - Enhancements that reduce language verbosity
  • Repeater - Message broadcasting, listening and repeating
  • NamedObject - Object naming



Packaging

Classes implementing this interface are provided with easy access to packages and package resources relative to the class' package:

  • PackageTrait.packageResource(String) - Returns a Resource for the given path relative to the class implementing this interface
  • PackageTrait.relativePackage(String) - Returns a KivaKit Package for the given path relative to the class implementing this interface



Registry

Access to this component's lookup Registry is provided and fulfills basic needs for object wiring:

  • RegistryTrait.lookup(Class) - Lookup the registered object of the given type, if any
  • RegistryTrait.lookup(Class, Enum) - Find the given instance of the given class, if any
  • RegistryTrait.require(Class) - Find an instance of the given class, throwing an exception if there is none
  • RegistryTrait.require(Class, Enum) - Find the given instance of the given class, throwing an exception if there is none
  • RegistryTrait.register(Object) - Register the given singleton object for lookup
  • RegistryTrait.register(Object, Enum) - Register the given instance of the given object for lookup
  • RegistryTrait.registry() - Retrieves the lookup Registry for this component



Language

Adds methods that help in general to extend KivaKit's expressive capabilities in the Java language

Functions

  • LanguageTrait.ifNonNullApply(Object, Function) - Null-safe version of Function.apply()
  • LanguageTrait.ifNullDefault(Object, Object) - The given value if it is non-null, the default value otherwise.

Validation

  • LanguageTrait.isFalseOr(boolean, String, Object...) - Broadcasts a Problem if the given value is not false
  • LanguageTrait.isTrueOr(boolean, String, Object...) - Broadcasts a Problem if the given value is not true
  • LanguageTrait.isNonNullOr(Object, String, Object...) - Broadcasts a Problem if the given value is null

Exceptions

  • TryTrait.tryCatch(UncheckedCode, String, Object...) - Executes the given code, broadcasting a problem if it throws an exception
  • TryTrait.tryCatchThrow(UncheckedCode, String, Object...) - Executes the given code, rethrowing any exceptions
  • SilentTryTrait.tryCatchDefault(UncheckedCode, Object) - Executes the given code, returning the given default if an exception occurs
  • #tryFinally(UncheckedCode, Runnable) - Executes the given code, always running the Runnable after execution

Result

  • ResultTrait.run(Code) - Executes the given code, capturing any messages broadcast during execution in a Result object



Settings

Settings for a component can be retrieved with SettingsTrait.settingsRegistry(). This provides a simplified interface to load settings objects specified by the user while also allowing for default settings when they are not specified. See Settings for details.

  • SettingsTrait.settingsRegistry() - Retrieves the Settings registry for this component
  • SettingsTrait.lookupSettings(Class) - A settings object of the specified class or null if none exists
  • SettingsTrait.lookupSettings(Class, Enum) - Get any given instance of the given settings object type
  • SettingsTrait.requireSettings(Class) - Gets the given settings object or fails
  • SettingsTrait.requireSettings(Class, Enum) - Gets the settings object of the given instance or fails
  • SettingsTrait.registerSettingsObject(Object) - Adds the given settings object
  • SettingsTrait.registerSettingsObject(Object, Enum) - Adds the given settings object
  • SettingsTrait.registerSettingsIn(SettingsStore) - Adds settings objects from the given settings store



Repeater

  • Listener.listenTo(Broadcaster) - Adds this component as a listener to the given Broadcaster
  • Broadcaster.addListener(Listener) - Adds the given listener to this component
  • Transceiver.announce(String, Object...) - Broadcasts an Announcement message
  • Transceiver.problem(String, Object...) - Broadcasts a Problem message
  • Transceiver.warning(String, Object...) - Broadcasts a Warning message
  • Transceiver.quibble(String, Object...) - Broadcasts a Quibble message
  • Transceiver.glitch(String, Object...) - Broadcasts a Glitch message
  • Transceiver.information(String, Object...) - Broadcasts an Information message
  • Transceiver.trace(String, Object...) - Broadcasts a Trace message if Transceiver.isDebugOn() is true for this component
